Can you guys stop being haters? Yes Idina was a little ahead of tempo but don't you know those things happen in live performance? There are a number of issues that may have caused this, from an off sync earpice or simply because she was nervous (which is totally understandable). But taking that and saying she is a terrible singer is just wrong. She has proven herself time and time as a great singer or have you people forgotten that she delivererd a fantastic elphaba on broadway (and won a Tony award for it) and also brought elsa to life (and won an Oscar for it).
Just chill and be a little more kind, she is an amazing singer and performer like it or not.
